<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>i3 FAQ - Individual question feed</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/questions/</link><description>Frequently asked questions and answers about the i3 window manager</description><atom:link href="http://faq.i3wm.org/feeds/question/3999/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright i3, 2012</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 26 Jun 2014 17:01:45 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Making hangouts extension always launch as float</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3999/making-hangouts-extension-always-launch-as-float/</link><description>The hangouts extensions title changes every time the name of the hangout itself is changed and it appears to lack a class value. Is there a way to always have the windows float instead of manually floating the window each time the name change?</description><pubDate>Mon, 16 Jun 2014 12:01:35 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3999/making-hangouts-extension-always-launch-as-float/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by kegluneq for &lt;p&gt;The hangouts extensions title changes every time the name of the hangout itself is changed and it appears to lack a class value. Is there a way to always have the windows float instead of manually floating the window each time the name change?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3999/making-hangouts-extension-always-launch-as-float/?answer=4037#post-id-4037</link><description>Try this rule in your .i3/config file:

`for_window [window_role="pop-up"] floating enable`</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Jun 2014 17:01:45 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3999/making-hangouts-extension-always-launch-as-float/?answer=4037#post-id-4037</guid></item></channel></rss>